This paper discusses approaches for efficient reasoning on large-scale data using OWL and its sublanguages, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database (cs.DB) research. The paper also discusses forward and backward chaining techniques, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions MapReduce, which is commonly used in distributed computing (cs.DL).
